# Terminal Operation Rules

## PowerShell Commands Priority

1. File Operations:
   - Create: `New-Item -Path <path> -ItemType File/Directory`
   - Write: `Set-Content -Path <path> -Value <content>`
   - Read: `Get-Content -Path <path>`
   - Remove: `Remove-Item -Path <path>`

2. Command Guidelines:
   - Prefer PowerShell native commands over Unix-style commands
   - Execute one operation per command
   - Use full parameter names for clarity
   - Implement error handling when necessary

